cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on security and privacy issues in computer networks, specifically in the context of Tor. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses network measurements and path prediction, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a new client for Tor, which involves load balancing and relay selection, which could fall under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the threat of traffic correlation attacks, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
